descript.abstract: Management areas shown here are either federal, state, or managed by The Nature Conservancy and potentially do not include all management areas within the study area, nor do they consider the level of protection per management area.

overview.eaover:
Notes on TNC Lands Categories
Fee Ownership - TNC holds all rights and manages the property for conservation
Conservation Easement- TNC controls the target species or community occurrences on the Tract through a perpetual, legally binding agreement that restricts activities on the property.
Deed Restrictions - TNC controls the target species or community occurrences on the Tract through retained rights in the deed-out. These retained rights typically needed to be re-recorded with the State's County Recording Office. A common duration before re-recording is necessary is 30 years, but varies state to state.
Conservation Management Agreements and Leases - Landowner has signed a legally binding lease, license or management agreement with TNC. Duration varies for each lease, license, or agreement.
